<subSubSection id="70E51A85FFB12578FF4BAEB9A962CE25" lastPageId="48" lastPageNumber="49" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" type="description">
<paragraph id="3840490EFFB12566FF4BAEB9AFBDC8A7" blockId="46.[151,1437,1490,1950]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis id="0A8B951CFFB12566FF4BAEB9AD93CAD7" bold="true" box="[199,420,1490,1517]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Description. Male.</emphasis>
Whole fly as 
<figureCitation id="A0C4558BFFB12566FDC8AEB8AE92CAD7" box="[580,677,1491,1517]" captionStart="FIGURES 283–286" captionStartId="46.[151,264,1384,1409]" captionTargetBox="[187,1400,385,1356]" captionTargetId="figure@46.[187,1400,381,1359]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="FIGURES 283–286. Megaselia zarghanii n. sp. male. 283, whole fly; 284, frons; 285, detail of frons; 286, left antenna, palp and proboscis. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573450" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573450/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Fig. 283</figureCitation>
. Frons as 
<figureCitation id="A0C4558BFFB12566FC94AEB8AF4ECAD7" box="[792,889,1491,1517]" captionStart="FIGURES 283–286" captionStartId="46.[151,264,1384,1409]" captionTargetBox="[187,1400,385,1356]" captionTargetId="figure@46.[187,1400,381,1359]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="FIGURES 283–286. Megaselia zarghanii n. sp. male. 283, whole fly; 284, frons; 285, detail of frons; 286, left antenna, palp and proboscis. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573450" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573450/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Fig. 284</figureCitation>
, with microtrichia restricted to edges (
<figureCitation id="A0C4558BFFB12566FAA1AEB8A9A7CAD7" box="[1325,1424,1490,1517]" captionStart="FIGURES 283–286" captionStartId="46.[151,264,1384,1409]" captionTargetBox="[187,1400,385,1356]" captionTargetId="figure@46.[187,1400,381,1359]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="FIGURES 283–286. Megaselia zarghanii n. sp. male. 283, whole fly; 284, frons; 285, detail of frons; 286, left antenna, palp and proboscis. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573450" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573450/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Fig. 285</figureCitation>
). Cheek with 5 bristles and jowl with 2 that are longer and more robust. Postpedicels, which lack SPS vesicles, palps and proboscis as 
<figureCitation id="A0C4558BFFB12566FED9AD70AD82C90F" box="[341,437,1563,1589]" captionStart="FIGURES 283–286" captionStartId="46.[151,264,1384,1409]" captionTargetBox="[187,1400,385,1356]" captionTargetId="figure@46.[187,1400,381,1359]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="FIGURES 283–286. Megaselia zarghanii n. sp. male. 283, whole fly; 284, frons; 285, detail of frons; 286, left antenna, palp and proboscis. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573450" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573450/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Fig. 286</figureCitation>
, the labella with only a few short spinules below. Thorax brown. Two notopleural bristles, with no cleft in front of these, and mesopleuron with short hairs (
<figureCitation id="A0C4558BFFB12566FCFBAD54AFEDC963" box="[887,986,1599,1625]" captionStart="FIGURES 287–296" captionStartId="47.[151,264,1862,1887]" captionTargetBox="[281,1308,181,1836]" captionTargetId="figure@47.[270,1317,181,1837]" captionTargetPageId="47" captionText="FIGURES 287–296. Megaselia zarghanii n. sp. male. 287, side of thorax; 288, scutellum; 289, left face of hypopygium; 290, left face of epandrium; 291, right face of epandium; 292, right face of hypandrium; 293, front tarsus; 294, front basitarsus; 295, hind femur; 296, wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573452" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573452/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Fig. 287</figureCitation>
). Scutellum with 4 bristles and a pair of hairs (
<figureCitation id="A0C4558BFFB12566FF50AD08AD09C947" box="[220,318,1635,1661]" captionStart="FIGURES 287–296" captionStartId="47.[151,264,1862,1887]" captionTargetBox="[281,1308,181,1836]" captionTargetId="figure@47.[270,1317,181,1837]" captionTargetPageId="47" captionText="FIGURES 287–296. Megaselia zarghanii n. sp. male. 287, side of thorax; 288, scutellum; 289, left face of hypopygium; 290, left face of epandrium; 291, right face of epandium; 292, right face of hypandrium; 293, front tarsus; 294, front basitarsus; 295, hind femur; 296, wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573452" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573452/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Fig. 288</figureCitation>
). Abdominal tergites brown with numerous fine hairs, with are a little longer at rear of T6 (
<figureCitation id="A0C4558BFFB12566FAA2AD08A9A7C947" box="[1326,1424,1635,1661]" captionStart="FIGURES 287–296" captionStartId="47.[151,264,1862,1887]" captionTargetBox="[281,1308,181,1836]" captionTargetId="figure@47.[270,1317,181,1837]" captionTargetPageId="47" captionText="FIGURES 287–296. Megaselia zarghanii n. sp. male. 287, side of thorax; 288, scutellum; 289, left face of hypopygium; 290, left face of epandrium; 291, right face of epandium; 292, right face of hypandrium; 293, front tarsus; 294, front basitarsus; 295, hind femur; 296, wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573452" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573452/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Fig. 289</figureCitation>
). Venter brown, and with hairs on segments 3–6. Hypopygium as 
<figureCitation id="A0C4558BFFB12566FCFEADECA838C99B" box="[882,1039,1671,1697]" captionStart="FIGURES 287–296" captionStartId="47.[151,264,1862,1887]" captionTargetBox="[281,1308,181,1836]" captionTargetId="figure@47.[270,1317,181,1837]" captionTargetPageId="47" captionText="FIGURES 287–296. Megaselia zarghanii n. sp. male. 287, side of thorax; 288, scutellum; 289, left face of hypopygium; 290, left face of epandrium; 291, right face of epandium; 292, right face of hypandrium; 293, front tarsus; 294, front basitarsus; 295, hind femur; 296, wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573452" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573452/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Figs 289–292</figureCitation>
, the hypandrium having a left lobe only but the bristle each side longer than usual (
<figureCitation id="A0C4558BFFB12566FD39ADC0AF5AC9FF" box="[693,877,1707,1733]" captionStart="FIGURES 287–296" captionStartId="47.[151,264,1862,1887]" captionTargetBox="[281,1308,181,1836]" captionTargetId="figure@47.[270,1317,181,1837]" captionTargetPageId="47" captionText="FIGURES 287–296. Megaselia zarghanii n. sp. male. 287, side of thorax; 288, scutellum; 289, left face of hypopygium; 290, left face of epandrium; 291, right face of epandium; 292, right face of hypandrium; 293, front tarsus; 294, front basitarsus; 295, hind femur; 296, wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573452" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573452/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Figs 291 &amp; 292</figureCitation>
). Legs brown. Fore tarsus with posterodorsal hair palisade on segments 1–4 and 5 clearly longer than 4 (
<figureCitation id="A0C4558BFFB12566FD66ADA4AF7FC9D3" box="[746,840,1743,1769]" captionStart="FIGURES 287–296" captionStartId="47.[151,264,1862,1887]" captionTargetBox="[281,1308,181,1836]" captionTargetId="figure@47.[270,1317,181,1837]" captionTargetPageId="47" captionText="FIGURES 287–296. Megaselia zarghanii n. sp. male. 287, side of thorax; 288, scutellum; 289, left face of hypopygium; 290, left face of epandrium; 291, right face of epandium; 292, right face of hypandrium; 293, front tarsus; 294, front basitarsus; 295, hind femur; 296, wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573452" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573452/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Fig. 293</figureCitation>
) and basitarsis with rows of small spinules (
<figureCitation id="A0C4558BFFB12566FAA3ADA4A9A7C9D3" box="[1327,1424,1743,1769]" captionStart="FIGURES 287–296" captionStartId="47.[151,264,1862,1887]" captionTargetBox="[281,1308,181,1836]" captionTargetId="figure@47.[270,1317,181,1837]" captionTargetPageId="47" captionText="FIGURES 287–296. Megaselia zarghanii n. sp. male. 287, side of thorax; 288, scutellum; 289, left face of hypopygium; 290, left face of epandrium; 291, right face of epandium; 292, right face of hypandrium; 293, front tarsus; 294, front basitarsus; 295, hind femur; 296, wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573452" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573452/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Fig. 294</figureCitation>
). Dorsal hair palisade of mid tibia extends about 0.63 times its length. Hairs below basal half of hind femur longer than those of anteroventral row of outer half (
<figureCitation id="A0C4558BFFB12566FD02AC7CAED8C80B" box="[654,751,1814,1841]" captionStart="FIGURES 287–296" captionStartId="47.[151,264,1862,1887]" captionTargetBox="[281,1308,181,1836]" captionTargetId="figure@47.[270,1317,181,1837]" captionTargetPageId="47" captionText="FIGURES 287–296. Megaselia zarghanii n. sp. male. 287, side of thorax; 288, scutellum; 289, left face of hypopygium; 290, left face of epandrium; 291, right face of epandium; 292, right face of hypandrium; 293, front tarsus; 294, front basitarsus; 295, hind femur; 296, wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573452" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573452/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Fig. 295</figureCitation>
). Hind tibia with 13–15 moderately differentiated posterodorsal hairs, without anterodorsals, and spinules of apical combs simple. Wings (
<figureCitation id="A0C4558BFFB12566FC74AC50A86FC86C" box="[1016,1112,1851,1878]" captionStart="FIGURES 287–296" captionStartId="47.[151,264,1862,1887]" captionTargetBox="[281,1308,181,1836]" captionTargetId="figure@47.[270,1317,181,1837]" captionTargetPageId="47" captionText="FIGURES 287–296. Megaselia zarghanii n. sp. male. 287, side of thorax; 288, scutellum; 289, left face of hypopygium; 290, left face of epandrium; 291, right face of epandium; 292, right face of hypandrium; 293, front tarsus; 294, front basitarsus; 295, hind femur; 296, wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573452" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573452/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Fig. 296</figureCitation>
) 
<quantity id="FF07E4EBFFB12566FBEAAC50A8FDC86C" box="[1126,1226,1851,1878]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.69" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" unit="mm" value="1.69">1.69 mm</quantity>
long. Costal index 0.44. Costal ratios 3.82: x1.47: 1. Costal cilia (of section 3) 
<quantity id="FF07E4EBFFB12566FCC0AC34AF87C840" box="[844,944,1887,1914]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" unit="mm" value="0.12">0.12 mm</quantity>
long. No vein 3 hair. 4 axillary bristles, the outermost being 
<quantity id="FF07E4EBFFB12566FEDFACE8AD80C8A4" box="[339,439,1923,1950]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" unit="mm" value="0.13">0.13 mm</quantity>
long. Sc not reaching R1. Haltere brown.
</paragraph>
<caption id="6C801986FFB02567FF1BAC2DADB6C89D" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573452" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3573452" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573452/files/figure.png" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" startId="47.[151,264,1862,1887]" targetBox="[281,1308,181,1836]" targetPageId="47">
<paragraph id="3840490EFFB02567FF1BAC2DADB6C89D" blockId="47.[151,1436,1862,1959]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis id="0A8B951CFFB02567FF1BAC2DAD5AC865" bold="true" box="[151,365,1862,1887]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">FIGURES 287–296.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="FFFF328DFFB02567FEF8AC2CAE73C865" authority="Khameneh &amp; Khaghaninia &amp; Disney &amp; Maleki-Ravasan, 2019" authorityName="Khameneh &amp; Khaghaninia &amp; Disney &amp; Maleki-Ravasan" authorityYear="2019" box="[372,580,1863,1887]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zarghanii" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="0A8B951CFFB02567FEF8AC2CAE73C865" box="[372,580,1863,1887]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Megaselia zarghanii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="0A8B951CFFB02567FDC7AC2CAEB2C865" bold="true" box="[587,645,1863,1887]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="11B82867FFB02567FDC7AC2CAEB2C865" box="[587,645,1863,1887]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
male. 287, side of thorax; 288, scutellum; 289, left face of hypopygium; 290, left face of epandrium; 291, right face of epandium; 292, right face of hypandrium; 293, front tarsus; 294, front basitarsus; 295, hind femur; 296, wing.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="3840490EFFAF2578FF4BABF3A962CE25" blockId="48.[151,1436,152,324]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis id="0A8B951CFFAF2578FF4BABF3AD6ACF89" bold="true" box="[199,349,152,179]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Recognition.</emphasis>
In the key to the 
<taxonomicName id="FFFF328DFFAF2578FDAAABF2AEACCF89" authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1856" box="[550,667,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0A8B951CFFAF2578FDAAABF2AEACCF89" box="[550,667,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Megaselia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
males of the British Isles (
<bibRefCitation id="5C6E34FFFFAF2578FC47ABF2A86ACF89" author="Disney, R. H. L." box="[971,1117,153,179]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" pagination="1 - 155" refId="ref21228" refString="Disney, R. H. L. (1989) Scuttle Flies-Diptera Phoridae Genus Megaselia. Handbooks for the Identification of British Insects, 10 (8), 1 - 155." type="journal article" year="1989">Disney 1989</bibRefCitation>
) it runs to couplet 72 lead 
<specimenCount id="2EF98287FFAF2578FA02ABF2AC81CFED" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" type="generic">
1 
<taxonomicName id="FFFF328DFFAF2578FF1BABD5AC81CFED" authority="(Wood)" authorityName="Wood" baseAuthorityName="Wood" baseAuthorityYear="1912" box="[151,182,190,215]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simulans">
<emphasis id="0A8B951CFFAF2578FF1BABD5AC81CFED" box="[151,182,190,215]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">M.</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</specimenCount>
simulans (Wood), but the brown legs and haltere rule out this species. In the key of 
<bibRefCitation id="5C6E34FFFFAF2578FBD2ABD6A93CCFED" author="Schmitz, H." box="[1118,1291,188,215]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" pagination="369 - 416" refId="ref22164" refString="Schmitz, H. (1956) Phoridae. In: Lindner, E. (Ed.), Die Fliegen der palaearktischen Region. 4 (33). Lieferung 187. E. Schweizerbart'sche Verlagsbuchhandlung, Stuttgart, pp. 369 - 416." type="book chapter" year="1956">Schmitz (1956)</bibRefCitation>
to Abteilung I it runs couplets 14 or 18 but its costa and costal cilia are too short. In 
<bibRefCitation id="5C6E34FFFFAF2578FC39AB8AA8A5CFC6" author="Borgmeier, T." box="[949,1170,225,252]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" pagination="257 - 416" refId="ref20921" refString="Borgmeier, T. (1964) Revision of the North American Phorid flies. Part II. The species of the genus Megaselia, subgenus Aphiochaeta (Diptera, Phoridae). Studia Entomologica, Petropolis, 7, 257 - 416." type="journal article" year="1964">Borgmeier’s (1964)</bibRefCitation>
key to Nearctic species Group I it runs to couplet 13, lead 
<specimenCount id="2EF98287FFAF2578FD96AA6EAE79CE25" box="[538,590,261,287]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" type="generic">
1 
<taxonomicName id="FFFF328DFFAF2578FDA3AA6DAE79CE25" authority="(Malloch)" authorityName="Malloch" baseAuthorityName="Malloch" baseAuthorityYear="1912" box="[559,590,262,287]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fenestrata">
<emphasis id="0A8B951CFFAF2578FDA3AA6DAE79CE25" box="[559,590,262,287]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">M.</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</specimenCount>
fenestrata (Malloch), but its palps are yellow and legs are yellowish.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="70E51A85FFAF2578FF4BAA42A8D6CE79" box="[199,1249,297,324]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="3840490EFFAF2578FF4BAA42A8D6CE79" blockId="48.[151,1436,152,324]" box="[199,1249,297,324]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis id="0A8B951CFFAF2578FF4BAA42AD79CE79" bold="true" box="[199,334,297,323]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Etymology.</emphasis>
Named after Dr. Ebrahim Zarghani (Former Ph.D. student of Prof. Khaghaninia).
</paragraph>
